snippet.textDisplay:
Are there people in Indian Punjab that still speak Punjabi in Saraiki dialect, or has it all merged into the same dialect? Anybody know? I am Punjabi as well, but our dialect is Pottohari, and I know our area had a lot of Sikh who migrated during partition, so I always wonder if they still speak in Pottohari dialect or not.


btw if you want to check out Pottohari dialect check out Chakwal Group on Coke studio Pakistan.
